# Standards MCP Rules for Cursor

## Overview
Cursor rules for the Standards MCP Server project.

## Context
- MCP server using @modelcontextprotocol/sdk
- STDIO transport (stdin/stdout communication)
- Provides 15 tools for arc42, OWASP, ISO standards

## Commands
```bash
npm install     # Install dependencies
npm run dev     # Run with --watch for development
npm start       # Run production
npm test        # Run tests via node --test
```

## Tool Categories
- **arc42**: Architecture documentation (12 sections)
- **OWASP ASVS**: Security requirements (L1/L2/L3 levels)
- **ISO 42010**: Architecture views (logical, deployment, operational, data, security)
- **ISO 9241**: Usability checklist (effectiveness, efficiency, satisfaction)
- **ISO 25010**: Quality model (8 characteristics)
- **Material Design 3**: Design tokens

## Anti-Patterns
- ❌ Modifying tool return shapes without updating tests
- ❌ Adding new standards without updating AGENTS.md
- ❌ Breaking stdio transport (server must remain stdin/stdout)